The Lagos State Government has revealed that a mother and her baby were among the patients discharged from the hospital on Friday. Prof. Akin Abayomi, Commissioner of Health in the state said this while confirming that the state recorded 11 new cases on Friday. Recall that Nigeria had announced that it recorded twenty new cases, making the number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in the country 210. However, Abayomi said, “Lagos Confirmed 11 new cases of COVID-19 on 3rd April, 2020, bringing the total confirmed cases in Lagos to 109. “The good news is that 4 more COVID-19 patients; 3 females and 1 male among whom are mother & her baby were discharged on 3rd April, 2020 “The number of COVID-19 patients who have fully recovered and discharged is now 23.”